The 155's were SP also. They moved frequently, but generally stuck to the better roads. The 105's were airdropped in remote FSB's, but were usually towed by truck. That's why we called them 105 towed's. 105's came in two varieties, single and split trail. The single trail were the older howitzers. In the split trail, the trail separated into a swallow tail and gave better stability in fire.<br><br>
We used to use 175 mm guns for high angle, and the 8&quot; howitzers for precision fire missions.<br><br>
Chet, what was your AO?<br><br>
